tweets_location = tweets_spark.filter(tweets_spark['location'].isNotNull()
                                     & (F.col("location") != "she/her")
                                     & (F.col("location") != "Earth")
                                     & (F.col("location") != "Global")
                                     & (F.col("location") != "Planet Earth")
                                     & (F.col("location") != "Everywhere")
                                     & (F.col("location") != "Worldwide"))
#taking out null values and she/her values

import cartopy.crs as ccrs
from matplotlib.patches import Circle
ax = plt.axes(projection=ccrs.PlateCarree())
ax.stock_img()
# plot individual locations                                                                                                       
ax.plot(mapdata.lon, mapdata.lat, 'ro', transform=ccrs.PlateCarree())
# add coastlines for reference                                                                                                
ax.coastlines(resolution='50m')
ax.set_global()
ax.set_extent([20, -20, 45,60])
def get_radius(freq):
    if freq < 500:
        return 0.05
    elif freq < 1000:
        return 0.4
    elif freq < 1500:
        return 0.7
    elif freq < 2000:
        return 1.0
    elif freq < 2500:
        return 1.3
    elif freq < 3000:
        return 1.6    
    elif freq < 3500:
        return 1.9
    elif freq < 6000:
        return 2.2
    elif freq < 10000:
        return 2.5
    elif freq < 13000:
        return 2.8
    elif freq < 16000:
        return 3.1
    elif freq < 19000:
        return 3.4
    elif freq < 22000:
        return 3.7
    elif freq < 25000:
        return 4.0
    elif freq < 40000:
        return 4.5  
    elif freq < 140000:
        return 8.0
# plot count of tweets per location
for i,x in locations.iteritems():
    ax.add_patch(Circle(xy=[i[2], i[1]], radius=get_radius(x), color='blue', alpha=0.6, transform=ccrs.PlateCarree()))
plt.show()

    if freq < 500:

        return 8.0
